benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: Valid Payload scenarios: successful POST with valid catalog XML and creation of a new catalog version (TC01, TC02, TC04, TC05, TC13), including proper 201 response and resource URL (Location header).
Header validation: coverage of required and optional headers, including missing/empty required headers (TC06, TC07) and scenarios with extra/additional headers (TC11, TC26).

Invalid payload coverage: malformed XML (TC08), empty body (TC09), whitespace-only XML (TC23), dangerous/malformed content (XXE) (TC17), partially corrupted payload (TC18), invalid content type (TC10), and encoding variations (TC29, TC28).
Content-Type and payload validation: tests for unsupported content type (TC10) and various payload formats/encodings (TC29, TC28).
Security testing: handling of dangerous content such as XXE (TC17).
Large/edge payloads: very large payload (TC12) and boundary value scenarios (TC30).
Performance/load testing: sequential and concurrent POST workloads (TC19, TC20).
Fault tolerance: network interruption (TC15) and backend service unavailability (TC16).
Regression/backward compatibility: regression tests and compatibility with older clients (TC21, TC22).
Accessibility: accessible response for assistive technology (TC31).
Extra/header/parameter handling: tests for extra headers (TC11) and extra query parameters (TC26).
Empty DB scenario: uploading when catalog database is empty (TC04).
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling tests (e.g., 429 responses under load).
500 Internal Server Error scenarios beyond 503 (e.g., database or service-layer failures).
Caching behavior validation for POST responses (ETag/Cache-Control where applicable).
Explicit idempotency/duplicate-submission depth beyond version duplication (e.g., repeated submissions handling).
Consistent verification of Location header presence across all successful 201 responses.
Explicit tests for missing authentication separate from invalid tokens (in addition to TC14).
recommendations: Add rate-limiting and throttling tests to validate 429 responses under high load (align with performance tests TC19/TC20).
Introduce 500 Internal Server Error negative tests (e.g., simulated DB/service failure) beyond the existing 503 case (TC16).
Add tests for caching headers where applicable on POST responses, and verify consistency of cache-related headers if implemented.
Expand idempotency coverage with repeated submissions and potential replays to confirm expected behavior.
Ensure Location header is asserted across all successful POST responses (not just TC01).
Clarify/extend authentication coverage with explicit missing-auth scenarios if distinct from token invalid cases (beyond TC14).
